# Patterns to exclude from the Helm chart package (`helm package .`)
# These files are useful in the repo but not needed inside the chart archive.

# Git internals
/.git/
/.github/
/.gitignore

# CI / lint tooling
/.yamllint.yml

# Standalone example values (users download these from the repo, not the package)
/examples/

# Standalone dashboard exports and alert rule files
# (The chart uses files/dashboards/ — these extras are for reference only)
#
# IMPORTANT: these patterns are anchored to the repo root (leading "/").
# Without the anchor, .helmignore uses gitignore-style matching, where
# "dashboards/" matches a directory of that name at ANY depth — silently
# excluding files/dashboards/ (the one templates/ actually loads via
# .Files.Get) from every packaged chart. That exact bug shipped for real:
# Files.Get returned an empty string, so the ConfigMap's dashboard JSON was
# "", and Grafana logged "failed to load dashboard ... error=EOF" on every
# provisioning tick — the dashboard silently never appeared. Caught by an
# actual `helm install` + checking Grafana's dashboard list, not by
# `helm template`, which shows the ConfigMap structure but not that its
# value silently rendered empty.
/dashboards/
/alert-rules/

# Community / legal docs — already exposed via ArtifactHub from Chart.yaml metadata
CONTRIBUTING.md
CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
SECURITY.md

# Packaged chart archives that may exist locally
*.tgz
charts/*.tgz

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.tmp
*.bak
*.swp
*~
